results.title: And...You're How Old?
results.description:
And...You're How Old?

It was a beautiful Saturday afternoon and after spending most of the morning at my favorite discount books and magazines store, I carried 2 shopping bags filled with my favorite read- goods/literature:

Highlights for Children
Mad Magazines
The Far Side
Comic books
Pocket dictionaries, blank journals
and of course...Cause-mop-oliton

I sat quietly at the bus stop drinking my usual almond milk and giggling at the humorous and entertaining memes, picture puzzles and Alfred Newman’s “What...Me Worry?” funny captions.

My bus arrived too quickly and I started to scramble gathering my stack of magazines...clumsily dropping a couple of them.

A young couple started to assist me as tho I was some old woman who needed help crossing the street and even proceeded to direct me towards the elderly section at the front of the bus.

I smiled and politely said, 

“No, thanks guys.  Age is in the Mind of the Older.”

and happily walked to the back of the bus...sat down and continued to enjoy my read-goods.  :)

Esther Monsalve 
The Angel Shop 

p.s.  the items displayed are not for sale in this etsy posting...just the short story called,  And...You're How Old?

Thank you.

Note: Please use MEMO, an editor writing software, in oder to open this digital file.
